============================================================
  SESSION SUMMARY
============================================================

Built a complete AI Startup Simulator web game with:
- Turn-based business simulation game
- React + TypeScript frontend
- Node.js + Express backend
- SQLite database
- OpenAI API integration
- 10+ game features (achievements, news, competitors, tech tree, market expansion, employees, IPO/acquisition)
- PWA support with offline mode
- Comprehensive UI with glassmorphism design

============================================================
  TIMELINE
============================================================

[Phase 1] Initial Project Setup
--------------------------------
- Created mini-game-demo folder
- Initialized Vite + React project
- Installed Tailwind CSS
- Built initial game with 8 decisions, 10 random events, 7 metrics

[Phase 2] Balance Testing & Patching
-------------------------------------
- Identified fundraising exploit (infinite $195K net gain per round)
- Added 3-layer fix: threshold gate, cooldown, diminishing returns
- Ran 10 strategy simulations via balance-test.js
- Found game was too hard (all strategies failed in 3-5 months)
- Rebalanced: doubled starting funds, reduced burn rate and costs
- Verified 6/10 strategies can now win

[Phase 3] TypeScript Refactoring
---------------------------------
- Migrated from JavaScript to TypeScript (strict mode)
- Created type definitions (types/game.ts)
- Extracted constants to config/constants.ts
- Split engine into modular files (calculator, validator, events, conditions, processor)
- Added Context + useReducer state management
- Added ErrorBoundary component
- Reorganized components into game/ and ui/ directories

[Phase 4] Backend Development
-------------------------------
- Built Express server with TypeScript
- Created SQLite database schema (users, games, game_history, leaderboard)
- Implemented JWT authentication (register/login)
- Added game CRUD operations with history tracking
- Integrated OpenAI API for AI-generated reports
- Added leaderboard system
- Created frontend API client

[Phase 5] Game Features
-------------------------
- Achievement system (14 milestones)
- Industry news (10 types)
- Competitor AI (3 strategies)
- Tech tree (10 technologies)
- Quarterly reports
- Market expansion (8 markets)
- Employee system (10 roles)
- IPO/Acquisition exit options

[Phase 6] UI/UX Improvements
------------------------------
- Glassmorphism design language
- Ambient glow background effects
- Icon badges with gradient backgrounds
- Loading skeletons for all components
- Offline mode with PWA support
- Responsive design

[Phase 7] Bug Fixes & Optimization
------------------------------------
- Fixed quarterly report display order
- Fixed acquisition offer duplicate companies
- Fixed quarterly report showing after game load
- Removed hover:scale effects causing layout overflow
- Added icon hover effects with fixed-size wrappers
- Relaxed test assertions for random events

[Phase 8] Audio, Mobile & Audit Fixes
---------------------------------------
- Added background music system with play/pause and volume control
- AudioProvider context for global audio state
- Volume persistence in localStorage
- Mobile optimization: responsive header, touch-friendly spacing
- Responsive grid layout (stacks on mobile)
- Fixed console.error only output in dev mode
- Replaced dynamic imports with static imports in GameBoard

============================================================
  KEY DECISIONS
============================================================

1. Game Balance:
   - Starting funds: $200K
   - Burn rate: $12K/month
   - Fundraising: gated by product/users, 3-month cooldown, diminishing returns
   - IPO requires: Month ≥ 24, Product ≥ 70%, Users ≥ 100, Funds ≥ $300K

2. Tech Stack:
   - Frontend: React 19 + Vite + Tailwind CSS v4 + TypeScript
   - Backend: Express + SQLite (better-sqlite3) + JWT
   - AI: OpenAI API with mock fallback
   - PWA: Service worker + manifest.json

3. Architecture:
   - Context + useReducer for state management
   - Modular engine (calculator, validator, events, conditions, processor)
   - Config-based features (achievements, news, competitors, tech tree, markets, employees)
   - Offline-first with localStorage fallback

